snippet.textDisplay:
VERSE


MOZZIK: 2X
Greedy girl,
You thought love is only about money,
You thought love is a joke,
Your name is, Greedy Girl.


TAYNA:
A greedy person you are,
You thought love is only for one night,
You thought you can buy me with money,
And then you call me, greedy girl.
--
(back and forth)


MOZZIK: 2X
Greedy girl.


TAYNA: 2X
But you are also, a greedy person.
--


TAYNA:
I wasn't born yesterday, I know what you want,
For a greedy desire of a night, you lose the one that you love,
That's why I'd rather cry in a Lambo than a truck,
But you can't call me a gold digger because I'm a don (boss) myself,
My life is good but I am not good,
This obsession, this fantasy, is there any loyalty,
But anyway, fuck it, at the end of the day I know you love me,
Even if I leave I know you'll come back,
So I don't care baby I'm after the paper (money),
I'll take care of myself so you can find the other girl,
But there's no one like me you're lying to yourself,
Ask yourself you'll hear the truth,
How idiotic this love was,
One glass of vodka, ---
Fuck this, fuck that, fuck you, I'm good on my own,
Don't text me anymore, there's no changes for again.


MOZZIK:


Incurable sickness.
For me you became unbearable,
I would have slapped you,
However, I'm not a person like that,
Why, why, why,
Why the fuck you ruin my sleep now,
When in some other days you wouldn't care,
You deleted my number,
Now my words touch your heart,
You started this bad, your ending will be bad,
And all that effort,
You tossed it, you stepped on it,
All of those good feelings, they left with the wind,
I taught her how to hold a knife, and now she stabbed me,
You can buy all of the other perfumes,
They won't be able to replace this smell,
How idiotic this love was,
One glass of vodka, fuck it,
I hate you because I loved you like an animal,
But whatever now,
I fell in love and I saw everything,
When my pocket got fuller,
My emotions left, I abandoned them at the beach,
But indeed in this life there's everything and all types of people,
And I don't want to see you ever again in my life.
